 <a href="/content/exploring-samsung-arm-chromebook-3g" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"><img src="http://www.linuxjournal.com/files/linuxjournal.com/ufiles/imagecache/teaser/nodeimage/story/11495f1.jpg" alt="" title=""  class="imagecache imagecache-teaser" width="100" height="100" /></a> 
  
  


      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/exploring-samsung-arm-chromebook-3g" title="Exploring the Samsung ARM Chromebook 3G">Exploring the Samsung ARM Chromebook 3G</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/bill-childers" title="View user profile.">Bill Childers</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Sep 19, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_867 first"><a href="/tag/chromebook" rel="tag" title="">Chromebook</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_891"><a href="/tag/chromeos" rel="tag" title="">ChromeOS</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_768"><a href="/tag/hacking" rel="tag" title="">hacking</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_328"><a href="/tag/mobile" rel="tag" title="">Mobile</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_20 last active"><a href="/tag/reviews" rel="tag" title="" class="active">Reviews</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/exploring-samsung-arm-chromebook-3g" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>
Back in late 2010, Google announced a "Chromebook"&mdash;a low-cost,
entry-level netbook that would run Google's own operating system,
ChromeOS. Google's vision of ChromeOS, although based on Linux, 
basically would be a giant Web browser, with all the apps on the machine running
in the browser.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/exploring-samsung-arm-chromebook-3g"> more>></a></span></p>
  </div>



  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_comments first last"><a href="/content/exploring-samsung-arm-chromebook-3g#comments" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">39 comments</a></li>
</ul>
